  "texts": [
    "This includes assessing the manufacturer's responsibility to create systems that cannot be used in hazardous ways.",
    "79 Recent lawsuits against Tesla illustrate this, with plaintiffs 76 For instance, a significant advancement in robotics in industrial production involves the shift from specialised robots designed to work in controlled environments with specific tasks to versatile robots capable of operating in diverse settings alongside humans and performing a wide range of tasks (Bozhinoski, 2019, 150 ref to Ford, 2016).",
    "77 The Uber accident report identified several factors that led to the crash, including Uber's insufficient safety risk assessment procedures, inadequate oversight of the driver, and a lack of effective mechanisms for addressing driver complacency caused by automation.",
    "The Tesla accident report similarly pointed to the limitations of the car's \"Autopilot\" function and ineffective monitoring of driver engagement, leading to complacency and inattention.",
    "See National Transportation Safety Board (2020)."
  ]
}